<br>
<br>
<br>
 <DIV class="poemtitle">The End Of Sacrifice</DIV><br>
  <div align="center"><img src="images/endsacrifice.jpg" width="300" height="350"><br>
  <a class="artistline" href="javascript:goauthor('copeland');">art by Kim Copeland</a></div>
<br>
<TABLE><TR><TD>
<br>
<br>


He gave us hands with palms for cupping breasts,<br />
With thumbs to censure serious mistakes<br />
Hubristic elders made upon the crests<br />
Of ancient hills.  Untainted glacial lakes<br />
 <br />
Hold promises young officers can't keep,<br />
Which disappoints platoons of soldiers sworn<br />
To constancy, who pledged their solemn, deep<br />
Commitment long before their sons were born.<br />
 <br />
A martial mind-set builds an inverse prison,<br />
A fortress raised to drive the inmates out.<br />
It is designed to stall the Enemy<br />
Until the darkness-ousting sun has risen,<br />
Refreshed by climes beyond the pale of doubt,<br />
And routs the shadows from Gethsemane.<br />
 <br />
A Calvary without a crucifix<br />
Is less redemptive than the River Styx,<br />
 <br />
Where episodes of disembodied sex<br />
Are sold to fallen souls on Charon's decks.<br />
<br /><br>
<br>

<a class="byline" href="javascript:goauthor('anderson')">by C.B. Anderson</a><br><br><br>
</TD></TR></TABLE>
